    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        This method creates a buffered reader to read in the text file line by line, converts the line to upper case characters and splits the line into words at all whitespaces. The words are then added to a buffer and placed into shingles and then each shingle is put on the blocking queue The buffer is then cleared for next use
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
